  "texts": [
    "Results for higher missing rates are in Table V. Note that except for our method (TSGM), CTFP, and GT-GAN, the other methods cannot deal with irregular time series, so we make it possible for them to operate on irregular settings by replacing RNN encoder with GRU-D.dimension of input dimension, and follow GTGAN [7] for other settings of NCDE-encoder and GRU-ODE-decoder.We follow default values for miscellaneous settings which are not explained on the baseline papers.",
    "Additionally, to deal with irregular time-series, we search the hyperparameters of GRU-D, which substitutes for RNN or are added to the head of baselines.",
    "We test the hidden dimension of GRU-D from 2 times to 4 times the dimension of input features.The following software and hardware environments were used for all experiments: UBUNTU 18.04 LTS, PYTHON 3.9.12, CUDA 9.1, NVIDIA Driver 470.141, i9 CPU, and GEFORCE RTX 2080 TI.",
    "C. Experimental ResultsAt first, on the regular time-series generation, Table IV shows that our method achieves remarkable results, outperforming most of the other baselines.",
    "Especially, for Stock, Energy, and Air, TSGM exhibits overwhelming performance by large margins for the discriminative score."
  ]
